  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Lifesaving Health Services to Drought Affected communities in selected woredas in Somali and Oromia Regions of Ethiopia.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the proposed project is to to reduce avoidable morbidity and mortality among drought affected communities in Somali and Oromia regions.WHO and partners will  implement activities related to management of severe acute malnutrition with medical complications, treatment of increasing number of endemic communicable diseases that threatens to reach epidemic levels especially among the most vulnerable drought affected communities such as IDPs and remote communities. WHO will aim at filling urgent emergency medical supplies gaps reported mainly from Somali and Oromia regions, WHO will procure and preposition 100  Emergency Health Kits (IEHK)  and 65 cholera kits based on the most urgent needs as identified by RHBs and WHO led regional Emergency Operation Centers. The project provides life-saving assistance to 33,303 people, including 8,152  women, 7,833  men and 17,318  children. This project will reach 5,861 People with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
